\pard\keepn\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\s6\sb60\sa60\kerning0\b\i\f2\fs19 Schedule\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\kerning1\b0\i0\f1\fs24 Meet for a 2 to 3 hour class session on two Friday evenings each month and meet for a class-plus-lab session for 3 to 5 hours on one weekend each month.  The course will go about three months.  Most sessions will be a mix of lecture, writing programs, making circuits, and running them.\par
\pard\keepn\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\s6\sb60\sa60\kerning0\b\i\f2\fs19 Course Plan\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\kerning1\b0\i0\f1\fs24 Background (sessions 1, 2)\par
\tab Math & binary numbers (refresher).\par
\tab Computers, microcontrollers, & embedded systems.\par
\tab C programming language basics (refresher).\par
MSP430FR6989 Dev Kit Basics (sessions 2, 3)\par
\tab Intro to the board:  layout; memory; pins; peripherals; etc.\par
\tab Intro to the IDE.\par
Using Digital Circuits with the Board (sessions 3,4,5)\par
\tab Digital inputs & outputs and circuits.\par
\tab Programming the digital I/O.\par
Using Timers and the Watchdog (sessions 5, 6)\par
\tab Types of timers & their applications.\par
\tab Watchdog timer & its application.\par
\tab Using the timers.\par
Using the Board to Create Devices (sessions 6, 7, 8)\par
Software Libraries to Improve Programs (sessions 8, 9)\par
